0:05:16.873,000 --> 0:05:19,000
So RKCP is an algorithm designed by Ray Kurzweil,

106
0:05:20.747,000 --> 0:05:22,000
who's a director of engineering at Google

107
0:05:22.993,000 --> 0:05:24,000
and a firm believer in artificial intelligence.

108
0:05:25.822,000 --> 0:05:28,000
So, you give RKCP a source text,

109
0:05:29.837,000 --> 0:05:33,000
it analyzes the source text in order to find out how it uses language,

110
0:05:34.33,000 --> 0:05:35,000
and then it regenerates language

111
0:05:36.302,000 --> 0:05:38,000
that emulates that first text.

112
0:05:38.854,000 --> 0:05:4,000
So in the poem we just saw before,

113
0:05:40.991,000 --> 0:05:42,000
Poem 2, the one that you all thought was human,

114
0:05:43.64,000 --> 0:05:44,000
it was fed a bunch of poems

115
0:05:45.214,000 --> 0:05:47,000
by a poet called Emily Dickinson

116
0:05:47.273,000 --> 0:05:49,000
it looked at the way she used language,

117
0:05:49.486,000 --> 0:05:5,000
learned the model,

118
0:05:50.675,000 --> 0:05:54,000
and then it regenerated a model according to that same structure.

